To ensure better understanding of history, it should be explained with detailed analysis beyond what is provided in PDFs. While those already familiar with the subject may not face difficulties, beginners often struggle without deeper explanations.
suggestions:
I feel that history and geography should be explained in more detail for better understanding. Currently, classes rely mostly on reading from PDFs with minimal explanation, especially in history, making it harder to grasp concepts fully. More in-depth discussions beyond the PDFs would make learning easier.

While those familiar with the subjects may understand easily, students like me, who come from a Bengali medium background, sometimes struggle to keep up in the English batch. My suggestion is to speak a bit slower while discussing answers during the short exam at the end of each class so that everyone can write them down properly.

This is just a suggestion, and I hope it does not create any issues for me.
